37)  NETWORK RECONFIGURATION
     STATUS:  ACTIVE  WALT.  PROGRESS HALTINGLY.
     MACHINE:  VARIOUS 940 AND 10 PROGRAMS.  MAY TAKE A LOT
     OF FILE SPACE ON VARIOUS MACHINES.
     TIME:  1-2 MAN MONTHS
     REQ:   NOW

     SUBPROJECTS:
     A)  ANAL. OF NET LOADING BY CIRCUIT-LEVEL SIMULATION
     AND SNAPSHOT DATA.
     B)  CHARACTERIZATION OF SESSIONS BY MACHINE, TERMINAL,
     SOURCE, ETC.  RAW DATA WILL BE FURNISHED BY ACCOUNTING.

38)  SNAPSHOT PROGRAM
     STATUS:  ACTIVE  BRYAN.  IMPROVEMENTS CONTINUALLY.
     NEXT RELEASE 1 FE     MACHINE:  INDEPENDENT 940 PROGRAM
     TIME:  2-3 WEEKS
     REQ:   NOW

     ADD A ROUTINE TO PRINT TIME AND DATE OF SNAP.
     ADD A COMMAND TO CHANGE THE OUTPUT FILE. (DONE)
     ADD XACT (EXCEPTIONAL CONDITIONS)
     ADD AC (ACT OVER ALL NODES)
     ADD GENERALIZED ACB (NODES NOT NECESSARILY ADJACENT)
     ADD ACP (ALL CIRCUITS PASSING THROUGH A GIVEN NODE)
     ADD ACA (ALL CIRCUITS IN A GIVEN NODE)

39)  SHELL-1108 LINK
     DORMANT.  NO SPEC.
     CORE: 4K
     TIME:  1 MONTH
     CPU:   MAY REQUIRE 1.0 MIC
     REQ:   NONE

     INTEGRATE 1108 INTERFACE INTO BASE CODE.

42)  ALLOW THE SUPERVISOR TO DO MULTIPLE DISC READS ON EACH
     DISPATCHING CYCLE IN ORDER TO RELEIVE LONG LOGIN QUEUES
     DURING PEAK PERIODS.

43)  WHEN THE SUPERVISOR CRASHES SAVE THE PAGES IN CORE
     PLUS THE PARAMETER TABLE PAGES.  THIS WILL HELP GREATLY
     (INSTEAD OF AN ARBITRARY COLLECTION OF PAGES) IN ANALYZING
     CRASHES.

44)  A PROGRAM TO TAKE SUPER CRASHES AND SAVE THEM IN A FILE.
     IN THIS WAY CRASHES CAN BE EASILY SAVED SO THAT THEY AREN'T
     LOST IF THE SUPER CRASHES AGAIN.  POSSIBILITY OF SOMEHOW 
     AUTOMATICALLY INITIATING THIS PROGRAM WHEN SUPER CRASHES.

45)  AT PRESENT TIME WHEN A TIMEOUT OCCURS DURING LOGIN, THE
     ENTRY IS REMOVED FROM THE LOGIN LIST BUT NOT FROM THE 
     DISK READ QUEUE.  THEREFORE DURING HIGH LOADS WHEN WE HAVE
     A LOT OF PEOPLE TIMING OUT BECAUSE THE QUEUES ARE SO
     LONG WE DO NOTHING TO RELEIVE THE LOAD.  WE STILL DO ALL
     THE DISK READS.  WE SHOULD REMOVE THE ENTRY FROM THE DISK
     QUEUE AT THE SAME TIME WE REMOVE IT FROM THE LOGIN LIST.
